channel.title: Need help with adding Models =P first time with PI
channel.description: Hey Moparscape!!!! Its Dylan XD here and i need some help! Its my first time using PI and I wanted to add Torva! well I know how to add the models into the Raw ( I think hehe ) and the only problem so far is that..... I cant find /* Hardcoded....*/ or the "switch (itemDef.id) {" in my itemDef.java.... and i dont think i have a itemDef_2.java... soooo..... if anyone could help me it would be GREAT!!!!

item.title: Need help with adding Models =P first time with PI
item.dc:creator: @whackatre Whackatre
item.description:
@whackatre wrote:

[quote=“Owner Zack of PwnageScape, post:10, topic:422769”][quote author=whackatre link=topic=525426.msg3826334#msg3826334 date=1322216519]

At the moment, let’s see. 32 total at the dead of the night. 5 donators, one owner, one admin. The reset are regulars. Jealous that you lost to people more mature than you? Grow up.

Please refrain from calling me a dumbass if you can’t even add the damn models properly.

The model system in Delta has worked for me for eleven months. They should work perfectly for PI as well.

If something’s not working here, it’s you.

@whac your an idiot. Don’t brag about a shitty server you’ve made in a post asking for help, no ones asked for it, its not necessary, just stop. If your going to post you could post something useful like helping the kid out. I like how your even more of an idiot saying that its just him. The problem is he is using DSPK or a more later version of DSPK, what i suggest is integrating a item_def2 and splitting up your item def. Now that’s just my opinion and theirs other ways to go with that but if you want help adding ints then that’s the only way i know possible.

Whac, if there were less of kids like you on moparscape, mopar might be a respectable community now a days.

Not bragging, just stating the truth. Stop butting into this, this was between Dylan and I.
He’s tried quite a few sources claiming they didn’t work. Are you sure it’s the programmers’s problem? Of course not.
Oh and yes, you were right when I forgot to help him out. Sorry, Dylan.
[/quote]
Funny how I’ve played his server for 11 months now, I think. And Mopar would be respectable if there were less kids like Justin? Are you kidding me? You mean the kids who can’t code and leech shit of everyone? Yeah, than mopar would be the best.[/quote]

Nice to see you on Mopar Zack,
Let’s stop posting, we’re not helping Dylan and Race at all.
